Elements of a form
-designing the form page

Whenever you want a text box for user input, you want a form
<form> </form>

-inside the form, you use the <input> tag to get user input 
"type" is an attribute that determines what type of user input box you want

DOM: document object model (a type of structure in memory)
-when rendering the page, a model of the document is built in memory
-each element = an object